    "title": "Open view from menu action in new tab", 
    "comments": [
        {
            "date": "2011-11-11 07:58:01", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "When you open a view from a menu option, it is better to open a new tab, as in gtk. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "We can thus move between open views as we want.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "For example, on a sale order go on history tab and open invoice. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Then try to return in original sale order. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Now it is impossible directly. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "You have to go back through the menu and search again for sale order.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Please take a look at Openbravo interface and take from there the idea of tabs in the web client.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "If it is too early to RC1, then at least try to make that menu options open in new browser tabs.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Thank you.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
